
The Decoder tool in Burp Suite is used to analyze and transform encoded, encrypted, or obfuscated data. This tool simplifies the analysis of data encountered during security testing. 
In addition to decoding, it also has capabilities to encode or encrypt data using existing methods.

• Entering Data
• Decoding Data
• Some Supported Encoding Methods
• Some Supported Hashing Methods


-- Entering Data --

• Manual Input: Data to be decoded can be directly typed or pasted into the text box in the Decoder tab.
• Sending from Other Tools: Data captured using other Burp Suite tools like Proxy or Repeater can be directly sent to Decoder using the "Send to Decoder" option.


-- Decoding Data --

In the Decoder interface, the format of the data to be decoded is selected.

• Smart Decode: Automatically detects and decodes the type of encoding.
• Unicode Encoding/Decoding: Converts text to Unicode codes or decodes from these codes to text.


-- Some Supported Encoding Methods --

• Decode URL
• Decode HTML
• Decode Base64
• Decode ASCII Hex
• Decode Hex
• Decode Octal
• Decode Binary
• Decompress GZIP


-- Some Supported Hashing Methods--

• MD2
• MD4
• MD5
• SHA-1
• SHA-256
• SHA-512


